        "StringValue": "Talisman's Special Solutions models the **NTWF ontology** from Jessica Talisman's *Intentional Arrangement* series — the workflow language for a fictional 1,100-person technology company, *Talisman's Special Solutions*. Instead of a pile of tutorial stubs, it tells **one complete story**: the *Production Deployment Workflow*. Five ordered steps carry a release from AI risk assessment to post-deploy report, passing through all three disjoint agent types — an AI Risk Analysis Agent (RiskAnalysis-AI, `risk-classifier-v2.4.1`); a human Legal Compliance Reviewer (James Okafor); a human Release Manager (Maria Gonzalez), who owns the approval gate that authorizes the release; and an automated CI/CD pipeline. Roles are kept separate from the agents who fill them (Heuristic 2), so a personnel change is one edge, not a workflow rewrite. A delegation chain (Release Manager -> VP Engineering -> CTO) handles escalation; a PROV provenance chain links five artifacts from risk report to post-deploy report; and a DCAT dataset feeds the AI step. Every NTWF class, property, and competency question is exercised by real, connected rows — answered by derived columns and first-class transitive-closure views (`precedesStep`, `delegatesTo`), with load-bearing INDEX/MATCH lookups resolving the role-to-agent indirection.",
