        "JsonValue": "[\"**CQ1 — steps in order.** Walk `StepPrecedence` from `prod-deploy-step-1`; the four asserted edges (1->2->3->4->5) imply the full transitive ordering, including the never-asserted 1->5.\", \"**CQ2 — who approves a deployment.** From the *Release Approval Gate* (step 3) to its assigned role (Release Manager) to the human who fills it: Maria Gonzalez.\", \"**CQ3 — AI vs human steps.** Two steps are executed by AI agents — step 1 (AI Risk Assessment, RiskAnalysis-AI) and step 5 (Post-Deployment Health Report, DeploymentHealth-AI) — and two require a human decision (`RequiresHumanApproval`): step 2 (Legal Review) and step 3 (Release Approval Gate). The deterministic CI/CD pipeline runs step 4 — a third, disjoint agent type, not counted as AI.\", \"**CQ4 — artifact provenance.** Follow `DerivedFromArtifact` from the post-deploy report back through deployment log, release authorization, legal clearance, to the risk report — five artifacts, four derivation links, one chain.\", \"**CQ6 — escalation.** When the Release Manager is unavailable, traverse `DelegatesTo`: Release Manager -> VP Engineering -> CTO. Note an AI role has no DelegatesTo edge — it cannot stand in a human delegation chain.\", \"**CQ7 — cross-department.** The Production Deployment workflow spans Engineering (six roles) and Legal (one role) — answerable by intersecting `Roles.OwnedBy`; exactly one step (Legal Review) is Legal-owned.\", \"**CQ8 — datasets and the AI that read them.** The Q1 2026 Risk Metrics dataset is `ConsumedBySteps` step 1, whose role is filled by RiskAnalysis-AI.\", \"**Read your first calculated field.** `Workflows.Name` is just `DisplayName` lowercased with dashes — but it lives in the rulebook, not in code. Rename the workflow and the slug updates in every substrate.\", \"**Trace a second-order rule.** `HasMoreThan1Step` reads the rollup `CountOfNonProposedSteps`, which counts `WorkflowSteps`. Two hops — the whole DAG in miniature.\"]"
